org.cef

Class CefBrowserSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cef.CefBrowserSettings

  • public class CefBrowserSettings
extends java.lang.Object
    Browser initialization settings. Specify NULL or 0 to get the recommended default values. The consequences of using custom values may not be well tested. Many of these and other settings can also configured using command- line switches.

    • Field Detail

      • windowless_frame_rate

        public int windowless_frame_rate
        The maximum rate in frames per second (fps) that CefRenderHandler::OnPaint will be called for a windowless browser. The actual fps may be lower if the browser cannot generate frames at the requested rate. The minimum value is 1 and the maximum value is 60 (default 30). This value can also be changed dynamically via CefBrowser#setWindowlessFrameRate
